    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_78317697" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/78317697" />
    <a title="Ruth" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/335159-ruth"><img alt="Ruth" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1491245404p2/335159.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/78317697?book_show_action=true">Nov 19, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ruth" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ruth" href="/user/show/335159-ruth">Ruth</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780805060126" href="/book/show/2050213.The_Appointment">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer78317697" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13098097490648264547">This is a book that will haunt me. I picked it shortly after HM won the Nobel, because I’d never even heard of her, let alone read anything by her. The Appointment starts out with a young woman summoned to an appointment with the Romanian secret police. We soon learn this is the latest in a long series of these appointments, and this time she’s packed her toothbrush and towel. She leaves so early there is no possibility of her being late, and as we follow her on her way she muses about the past—</span>
  <span id="freeText13098097490648264547" style="display:none">This is a book that will haunt me. I picked it shortly after HM won the Nobel, because I’d never even heard of her, let alone read anything by her. The Appointment starts out with a young woman summoned to an appointment with the Romanian secret police. We soon learn this is the latest in a long series of these appointments, and this time she’s packed her toothbrush and towel. She leaves so early there is no possibility of her being late, and as we follow her on her way she muses about the past—about why the police are so interested in her, about her father’s infidelities, her friend shot trying to escape, the slimy investigator assigned to her case, her first husband who caused her grandparents to be deported. Meanwhile the tension builds.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13098097490648264547" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


